Description: Fragment from the wall of a glazed composition vessel (?), the exterior inscribed with a horizontal register of hieroglyphs.
Findspot: Found/Acquired: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 3 ? (?)
Curator's comments: A Findspot number 3 is pencilled on the internal wall of the sherd, inferring a possible provenance from Tell Dafana, though not specified in the Museum register.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.53, p.174, pl.16)
